==English==
===Verb form===
'''hacking'''
# [[present participle]] and [[gerund]] formed from the verb ''to [[hack]]''.

===Noun===
'''hacking'''
# Modifying the source code of a program such as an operating system.
# Black-Hat hacking (See [[cracking]]) is the [[unauthorized]] access to [[computer]] [[system]]s. 

====Usage note====
The "black hat" definition of [[hacking]] is considered offensive to many self-proclaimed hackers.  While both definitions are widely accepted, the community of "white hat" hackers consider their counterparts to not be hackers at all.

